Package gw.api.filters

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IBeanFilter
    Filter for lists or arrays of data, where the entire data set is in memory
    IFilter
    Used to mark objects which filter sets of information.
    IQueryFilter
    Filter for queries It is rare to implement this interface directly, prefer StandardQueryFilter which automatically handles tricky cases such as group queries (for example unions and intersections)
    StandardBeanFilter.ObjectFilter
    ObjectFilter interface
    StandardQueryFilter.QueryFilter
    ObjectFilter interface
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ConsistencyCheckTypelistFilterSet
    FilterSet which includes all of the possible string values as filter values.
    FilterSetBase
    Base class for filters sets.
    NameValueFilter
    A specialized IFilter that provides filters to backing data in the form of property + operation + value.
    StandardBeanFilter  
    StandardQueryFilter
    This class allows for the definition of new query filters.
    StandardQueryFilters
    A collection of simple filter classes that cover common situations.
